OL,3,CCall for action after 'devastating'
OL,4,Crise in drink deaths
OL,6,FThere has been a "catastrophic" rise
OL,7,Fin deaths caused by drinking, leading
OL,8,Fpublic health experts have said.
OL,10,FThe Alcohol Health Alliance (AHA) has
OL,11,Fcalled for urgent action from the
OL,12,FHealth Secretary to redress the
OL,13,F"alarming trend".
OL,15,FIn a letter to Wes Streeting, the
OL,16,FAlliance ` which is made up of medical
OL,17,Froyal colleges, charities, treatment
OL,18,Fproviders and academics ` highlights
OL,19,Fhow deaths caused "solely by alcohol
OL,20,Fhave increased by a catastrophic 42%
OL,21,Fsince 2019".
