OL,6,F"After decades of inaction, we urge
OL,7,Fyou to make it your New Year's
OL,8,Fresolution to redress this alarming
OL,9,Ftrend and stop needless suffering of
OL,10,Fcountless individuals, their children,
OL,11,Ffamilies and communities across the
OL,12,Fcountry.
OL,14,F"In 2023, 8,274 people lost their
OL,15,Flives to alcohol: the sharp end of a
OL,16,Fspectrum of harm that ripples through
OL,17,Fsociety and is putting growing
OL,18,Fpressures on our economy and health
OL,19,Fservices.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
